</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="389729C2671232439F865FD5C3AB7573" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">A-C</emphasis>
holotype, left palp; 
<emphasis id="158B0BFED94D4820D0EE3CDCA1B037B8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">D, E</emphasis>
paratype, right palp. 
<emphasis id="B6BE0297DEC85091BA661A8721BA0778" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">A</emphasis>
prolateral 
<emphasis id="3E3FDB165C983356E961BF514D00D7B9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">B</emphasis>
ventral 
<emphasis id="AD05FA2C66C16C7E4C49A121A4847463" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">C</emphasis>
retrolateral 
<emphasis id="0414BF94C39BA1261288EFB84D641948" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">D</emphasis>
bulb, retrolateral 
<emphasis id="FE258D836EDD26CC08C9D449E3E830A4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">E</emphasis>
same, ventral 
<emphasis id="222E029F31F13F36A4CD39B482FCE091" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">F</emphasis>
same prolateral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E75A289CB97B50133096983DC421A85B" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6340B4EDEA2A4AE608D20EC53A1ECFCB" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp of Dendroicius hotaruae sp. nov. A-C holotype, left palp; D, E paratype, right palp. A prolateral B ventral C retrolateral D bulb, retrolateral E same, ventral F same prolateral." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.952.51849.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/435131" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">3A-F</figureCitation>
) patella dark brown, slightly wider than long, covered with setae; tibia slightly wider than long, retrolateral tibial apophysis slightly longer than wide, lateral terminal apophysis darker, serrated along edge, dorsal tibial apophysis with small, serrated mesal branch; cymbium longer than wide, slightly longer than the length of the bulb in retrolateral view; bulb longer than wide, with sperm duct extending along margin; embolus short, half as long as bulb, needle shaped; dorsal embolic apophysis small, one fifth the length of embolus; tegular sclerite sheet-like, adjacent to dorsal embolic apophysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8370FC31993ECEE6AEBA8ACA2EE4D3C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="239FE45037614BD581D9DFBF3B714CAE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6A12F45E6EB6920552657581A6B404E8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Dendroicius hotaruae sp. nov., female paratype and male holotype. A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal C male holotype habitus, dorsal D same, lateral E female paratype habitus, dorsal F same, lateral G prolateral view of male left leg I H ventral view of female chelicerae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.952.51849.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/435132" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">4A, B, E, F, H</figureCitation>
). Total length 3.52. Carapace 1.38 long, 0.90 wide. Abdomen 2.13 long, 1.09 wide. Clypeus 0.05 high. Eye sizes and inter-distances: AME 0.28, ALE 0.16, PLE 0.09, AERW 0.79, PERW 0.88, EFL 0.62. Legs: I 1.63 (0.55 + 0.62 + 0.26 + 0.20), II 1.40 (0.46 + 0.52 + 0.24 + 0.18), III 1.55 (0.49 + 0.48 + 0.30 + 0.28), IV 2.13 (0.66 + 0.75 + 0.39 + 0.33). Appearance of abdomen and legs as in male but carapace with two pairs of white setal latero-marginal stripes from lateral sides of AME and two longitudinal stripes of white setae from AMEs along PLE to the rear margin of carapace. All legs yellow and abdomen laterally with black pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B40E9CC42F3CC903A12EA4F856AD15C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Epigyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0461F54826F2BBAA4E39F1228550EBE1" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Dendroicius hotaruae sp. nov., female paratype and male holotype. A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal C male holotype habitus, dorsal D same, lateral E female paratype habitus, dorsal F same, lateral G prolateral view of male left leg I H ventral view of female chelicerae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.952.51849.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/435132" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">4A, B</figureCitation>
) wider than long, with a wide hood posteriorly; copulatory openings circular; copulatory ducts long, curved medially; accessory gland indistinct; spermathecae oval; fertilization ducts folded 90°, well-developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="565B79E82D4EC588AB980A2858F60479" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
